<br>
TOTAL: 42 Cards  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This deck works best when you go first and most of the time you will either by your opponent&#39;s choice or yours.<br>
<br>
Remember, don&#39;t forget to get the Weave Powder into your starting hand for each of your Magi.  Try to play Drowls before getting to Marella in order to reap their full benefit.  Save Podys and Quallons for Quirle just in case you need to stall TEMPORARILY and obtain a Juntertrug Horn for Marella.  The Juntertrug Horn helps to bypass her Vapid effect.  Try to save Stealth in order to combine with The Hunt on Juntertrugs to quickly wipe out opposing creatures.  The other relics and spells are used for defensive purposes.<br>
<br>
Beginning with Kolte, play the Juntertrug Horn and immediately use it to grab a Juntertrug from your deck.  Next, play the Juntertrug and nothing else.  Don&#39;t forget to play the Weave Powder and end your turn.<br>
